Barronelle Stutzman was fined $1,000 in March for refusing to sell a gay couple flowers for their 2013 wedding . 
  The 70-year-old owner of Arlene's Flowers and Gifts in Richland, Washington cited her religious beliefs as the reason . 
  An online campaign has raised over $87,000 for the florist . 
  A judge ruled in February that her refusal was a violation of anti-discrimination laws . 
 